{
  "texts": [
    "This has the advantage that highly non-linear mappings between eye images and gaze can be accommodated for, and may lead to more accurate and robust gaze estimation (Cheng et al., 2024).",
    "However, these advantages may come at the cost of requiring large training datasets to infer these mappings.",
    "Moreover, deep learning methods are often regarded as 'black boxes', making it challenging to understand why the gaze estimation produced an inaccurate value or failed completely.",
    "As seen in the previous section, there are many different types of eye trackers available, each designed to estimate various aspects of gaze behavior.",
    "These eye trackers are offered by commercial companies and developed by research groups as open-source projects."
  ]
}